HEADWORD: Suaviloquent
<hw>Sua*vil"o*quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>suaviloquens</ets>; <ets>suavis</ets> sweet + <ets>loquens</ets>,
p. pr. of <ets>loqui</ets> to speak.]</ety> <def>Sweetly speaking; using
agreeable speech.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

